(111, 1, '2018-03-31 19:01:57', '2018-03-31 19:01:57', '<h1>Cases</h1>\r\nThere are seven cases: Nominative, Possessive, Possessed, Locative, Instrumental, Accusative, and Dative.\r\n\r\nThey are declined for plurality with the exception of Possessed.\r\n<h3>Nominative</h3>\r\nSingular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">sY-</span>\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">i</span>\r\n\r\nPlural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">sut-</span>\r\n<h3>Possessive</h3>\r\nSingular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">sEti-</span>\r\n\r\nPlural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">sEmi-</span>\r\n<h3>Possessed</h3>\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-kose</span>\r\n<h3>Locative</h3>\r\nSingular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-sI</span>\r\n\r\nPlural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-sEt</span>\r\n<h3>Instrumental</h3>\r\nSingular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">gjo-</span>\r\n\r\nPlural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">gjeV</span>\r\n<h3>Accusative</h3>\r\nSingular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">gu-</span>\r\n\r\nPlural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">gid-</span>\r\n<h3>Dative</h3>\r\nSingular-\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">ku-</span>\r\n\r\nPlural\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">kit-</span>\r\n<h2>Verb Inflections</h2>\r\nVerbs are inflected for Mood, Person, Tense, and Aspect.\r\nFirst Person Singular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-e</span>\r\n\r\nThird Person Singular -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-t</span>\r\n\r\nThird and First Person Plural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-Y</span>\r\n\r\nSecond Person Singular and Plural -\r\n\r\n<span class="koitekok_font">-i</span>\r\n<h2>Moods</h2>\r\nThe most common word order is VSO for Indicative Mood, if you switch the subject and verb, you get the Interrogative Mood.\r\nFor imperative, see verb inflections below', 'Koitekok Grammar', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '65-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-31 19:01:57', '2018-03-31 19:01:57', '', 65, 'https://koitekok-blog-thepog